    "Task 4 — Stats on real-ish data\n",
    "Create an array representing 10 student exam scores: scores = np.array([72, 85, 60, 91, 78, 55, 88, 74, 67, 95]). Find the mean, median, highest score, lowest score, and the index of the highest scorer. Then use np.where to label each student as \"pass\" (≥70) or \"fail\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "e364681c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "76.5\n",
      "\n",
